{
  "texts": [
    "Based on our observations, only one work, IC3Net [48], tests competitive settings and enables agents to compete for rewards.",
    "7IC3Net shows that competitive agents communicate only when it is profitable, e.g., before catching prey in the predator-prey domain.",
    "ℜ-MACRL [66] considers communication from malicious agents to improve the worst-case performance.",
    "In ℜ-MACRL, the whole environment is cooperative while agents learn to defend against malicious messages.",
    "Although the environment is cooperative, we classify this work under the competitive category as the learning goal between malicious agents and other agents is competitive."
  ]
}